            "description": "🔐 SECURITY ARCHITECTURE - Document Processor Access\n\n**KEY PRINCIPLE: Port 8070 is NOT exposed to the host machine**\n\n✅ CORRECT ACCESS (Recommended):\n   • Use API Gateway (port 8000)\n   • Send user JWT token\n   • Gateway validates user token\n   • Gateway generates service JWT\n   • Gateway proxies to internal Document Processor\n   • See Section 9 for examples\n\n❌ DIRECT ACCESS (NOT from host):\n   • Port 8070 is internal-only (no port mapping in docker-compose.yml)\n   • NOT accessible from localhost:8070 ❌\n   • Only accessible from within Docker network\n   • Only for internal service-to-service communication\n   • Only for testing from other containers\n\n🧪 TESTING INTERNAL ACCESS (For debugging):\n   If you need to test from within Docker network:\n   \n   ```bash\n   # From API Gateway container\n   docker exec am-am-api-gateway-1 python3 -c \\\n     \"import urllib.request; print(urllib.request.urlopen('http://am-document-processor:8070/api/v1/documents/types').read().decode())\"\n   ```\n\n**SECURITY BENEFITS:**\n✅ Client must authenticate with user JWT first\n✅ Service tokens never leave internal network\n✅ API Gateway controls all access to internal services\n✅ Prevents direct unauthorized access\n✅ Audit trail through API Gateway\n\n**ENDPOINTS:**\n   Public (no auth):\n   - GET /api/v1/documents/types\n   - GET /actuator/health\n   - GET /swagger-ui/**\n   \n   Protected (service JWT):\n   - POST /api/v1/documents/process\n   - POST /api/v1/documents/batch-process\n   - GET /api/v1/documents/status/{id}"
          },
